  "title": "Buyer/Appraiser (Luxury Good) - Up to S$4.5k",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Title: Luxury Goods Buyer/Appraiser</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Working Location: CBD, Singapore</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Working Hours: 5-day work week (Fixed Sundays Off) [Mon-Fri: 9.30am to 6.30pm, Sat: 9am to 6pm]</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Purpose:</strong></p>\n<p>Our client is seeking a motivated individual to join their team as a <strong>Luxury Goods Buyer / Appraiser</strong>, focusing primarily on the purchase of pre-loved luxury handbags and other high-end fashion items.<br>\n<br>\nThe successful candidate will work in a customer-facing environment, supporting the assessment and acquisition of second-hand luxury products. Prior experience in buying or appraisal is welcome, but not required—training will be provided.<br>\n<br>\nSince many of their customers are Japanese, this role requires interaction in Japanese during daily operations. Therefore, conversational-level Japanese is necessary to perform the job effectively.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assess and evaluate the authenticity, condition, and market value of second-hand luxury handbags and related items.</li>\n  <li>Interact with customers in-store and online regarding purchase inquiries.</li>\n  <li>Conduct simple cleaning or touch-ups on acquired products.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate repairs with external partners when necessary.</li>\n  <li>Record purchased items accurately in the internal inventory system.</li>\n  <li>Stay updated on luxury fashion trends, pricing, and product knowledge.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate closely with team members to ensure smooth store operations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conversational-level Japanese (as needed to liaise with Japanese-speaking customers).</li>\n  <li>Strong interest in luxury fashion, designer brands, and pre-owned goods.</li>\n  <li>Good communication skills and a customer-oriented mindset.</li>\n  <li>Willingness to learn appraisal procedures and product knowledge.</li>\n  <li>Able to work well with a team in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Nextbeat Singapore Pte. Ltd.</p>\n<p>EA License Number: 22C1267</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110252</p>",
